    <div class="elementListBrownSeparator"></div>



  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2559631136" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2559631136" />
    <a title="Jarek &quot;the Mistborn&quot; Dąbrowski" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/50223677-jarek-the-mistborn-d-browski"><img alt="Jarek &quot;the Mistborn&quot; Dąbrowski" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1450429421p2/50223677.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2559631136?book_show_action=true">Nov 06, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jarek &quot;the Mistborn&quot; Dąbrowski" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jarek &quot;the Mistborn&quot; Dąbrowski" href="/user/show/50223677-jarek-the-mistborn-d-browski">Jarek &quot;the Mistborn&quot; Dąbrowski</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50223677-jarek-the-mistborn-d-browski?shelf=read-in-2018">read-in-2018</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2559631136" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6055470308584004384">Really nice:) The topic of pandemic brought me to this book and i think the author did a really good job in explaining and showing how the different organizations like CDC or WHO work in a crisis situation. Compelling characters and a good dose of action. I took away one star because for me it was a little bit longer then it should be. Overall cool read. 4 stars:)</span>

          </span>
        </div>


